Got roast duck red curry, pad see ew with pork, and steamed shrimp shumai. The shumai were very blah – didn’t even finish them. One of the shrimps had black gunk inside it - the digestive track; certainly not the end of the world, but not very appetizing. The duck was good, and curry flavorful but a bit watery. The noodles were too limp – I prefer them with more bite, but their (and the pork’s) taste was good – but badly needed salt. Overall around average, I suppose.

WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE AND TREATMENT: Yesterday I ordered from Thaitation and parked in their established parking spots meant for customers in order to pick up the food. Since the food had to be eaten off the premises due to COVID-19, I did. When I returned to my car 20-30 minutes later, I learned it had been towed.  When I asked the restaurant about it, they stated they didn't call to have it towed and rather said that the tow company came to them asking to tow the car. They refused to pay any compensation for the $160.00 tow claiming that they were not responsible for the tow, despite me showing them proof I had been there to pick up food. I spoke to the owners and their nephew during that conversation.  I called the tow company that stated that the restaurant was lying and indeed they had called to purposefully tow the car. When I arrived to pick up the car, the towing company had said he spoke to the owners nephew (the one I had talked to earlier) and asked why he had told me that he didn't call. He said it didn't matter and that the car needed to be towed. He in fact lied about calling for the tow and blamed the towing on the towing company.  I paid the $160.00. I called them today and they changed their story three different times. They blamed me for parking there all night and day (I don't live in Boston and didn't visit Boston until that day), then stated that they never called and then stated that the spots were only for when the restaurant was open for patrons inside. Boston has limited parking and I was following the signs. They refused to reimbursement and stated that it was my fault for parking there (despite it being an established spot for their customers).  I have receipts to show that I have eaten there. This was the most expensive Thai food I've ever had including my tow.  I will never eat from there again.  Multiple lies and much disrespect.

Sorry, but I don't think I'll be going back there anytime soon.
